ning or closing or sounds like it is going to fall off the track the problem is most often the pulleys.";i:9;s:31:"There are two types of pulleys.";i:10;s:40:"Press Fit Pulleys and Cast Iron Pulleys.";i:11;s:119:"Most companies use a press fit pulley which is made up of two separate pieces attached by ball bearings onto the inner.";i:12;s:29:"Garage door jerks on opening.";i:13;s:99:"I have tried limit and force adjustments and checked door movement in tracks not sticking to floor.";i:14;s:73:"I had a chain come off the sprocket on my chamberlain garage door opener.";i:15;s:42:"I loosened the nuts to allow me to put it.";i:16;s:34:"So the opener has only one choice.";i:17;s:78:"That is to treat the garage floor as an obstruction triggering the re-opening.";i:18;s:67:"Your down limit switch is adjusted on the edge of working properly.";i:19;s:74:"Sometimes it forces the door on to the garage floor sometimes it sees the.";i:20;s:163:"An operator arm that is too positioned too long to the door will tend to pull the door horizontally rather than pull the door vertically when opening is initiated.";i:21;s:61:"Shorten the connection and the it should correct the problem.";i:22;s:104:"If you hear a loud thumping sound when opening and closing the door this is the sign of a serious issue.";i:23;s:32:"Typically it is a broken spring.";i:24;s:56:"To see if this is the problem look over the garage door.";i:25;s:68:"If the door has a broken spring it needs to be replaced immediately.";i:26;s:140:"However if you have a double door it is unlikely that both springs will break at the same time and your door will open with just one spring.";i:27;s:61:"Why Does My Garage Door Reverse as Soon as It Hits the Floor.";i:28;s:145:"Your garage door is likely the largest opening on your homes exterior so its important to have the peace of mind that it is functioning properly.";i:29;s:112:"One question some homeowners ask is why their garage door closes then immediately reverses to the open 